725508f-a.title: Queens: 59th Place - 56th Drive
725508f-a.text:
59th Place (foreground), between 56th Drive (left, not chown) and
Maspeth Ave. (right). Shown at the left foreground is an old farmhouse
occupied by one Eolyer in 1875 and owned by the following F. Divine
1860, Schwigert 1873, and Van Mater in 1891. When 60th Street, formerly
Aashington Place, was extended, the house was moved west about 10O feet.
It now occupies lots 105 and 107, the location in this view. At the
right, partially shown is an old home demolished prior to 1929. Under
construction in the background is P.S. 72 opposite 60th Street.
March 1923.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
